helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,
[image: Image_251120_094258.jpeg]
[image: Image_251120_094317.jpeg]
[image: Image_251120_094049.jpeg]
[image: IMG_3796.jpeg]

I am writing to follow up on my complaint regarding the missing Rybelsys
7mg medicine that I ordered from your platform. When I opened the package
in the morning to take the medicine, I was shocked to find it empty.
Immediately, I contacted your customer support team and filed a complaint.
The ticket ID for reference is 22205153.

It has now been 12-15 days since I raised the issue, and I have not
received a single call from your team. Every time I call customer care, I
am told that my issue will be resolved within 24-48 hours and the amount
will be credited to my PharmEasy account. However, I have not received any
updates or calls from your side. This delay and lack of response is very
frustrating and disappointing.

In my previous experiences with your company, I never faced such problems.
I have always received prompt service, but this time, I am being ignored. I
request you to resolve this issue at the earliest by either transferring
the amount to my account or providing the medicine as per my order.

Please take immediate action to resolve this matter and update me
accordingly.

Looking forward to your prompt response.
-- 
*Thanks & Best Regards,*
*Lucky Singh *
*+91-9818364837*

--

Dear PharmEasy Support Team,




I am writing to follow up on my complaint regarding the missing Rybelsys 7mg medicine that I ordered from your platform. When I opened the package in the morning to take the medicine, I was shocked to find it empty. Immediately, I contacted your customer support team and filed a complaint. The ticket ID for reference is 22205153.
It has now been 12-15 days since I raised the issue, and I have not received a single call from your team. Every time I call customer care, I am told that my issue will be resolved within 24-48 hours and the amount will be credited to my PharmEasy account. However, I have not received any updates or calls from your side. This delay and lack of response is very frustrating and disappointing.
In my previous experiences with your company, I never faced such problems. I have always received prompt service, but this time, I am being ignored. I request you to resolve this issue at the earliest by either transferring the amount to my account or providing the medicine as per my order.
Please take immediate action to resolve this matter and update me accordingly.
Looking forward to your prompt response.
--
Thanks & Best Regards,
Lucky Singh

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear pharmeasy team
I am very much disappointed by your customer service. I have being a
customer of your service since 2024 and I have ordered multiple medicines
from your site for our family members. But I have ordered a medication for
my grandfather who is a heart patient( order id 653430280709210112) on 28th
November on urgent basis. Also I ordered same medication for last 1 year.
But ordered delayed due to your doctor could not reached me and when ever I
call your customer care I show that your service will reach me in some
hour. Why should you delayed mu medicine which I have been ordered for last
1 year. It's regular for my grand parents. So call me ASAP or else I will
shift my monthly ordered to any other online store. I am a plus member of
your shopping site. For your reference I attached the screenshot of my
order.

Regards
Rajdeep Behera
8594802058

--

notes.body: Hello Rajdeep,     Greetings from PharmEasy!  We understand your concern in regard to order #653430280709210112-87065. We have highlighted your concern. We will notify you once we get a further update. We apologise for the inconvenience caused to you. Your patience is highly appreciated in the meantime.      You can also contact the numbers 080-46161170 or 080-61972566 to avoid any delay from your delivery phone number. You will only be able to call the doctor from the delivery number that is updated on the order. Please save these numbers so that it doesn't get marked as Spam and our team does not fail to connect.   Regards, PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Rajdeep,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

We understand your concern in regard to order #653430280709210112-87065. We have highlighted your concern. We will notify you once we get a further update. We apologise for the inconvenience caused to you. Your patience is highly appreciated in the meantime. 

You can also contact the numbers 080-46161170 or 080-61972566 to avoid any delay from your delivery phone number. You will only be able to call the doctor from the delivery number that is updated on the order. Please save these numbers so that it doesn't get marked as Spam and our team does not fail to connect.

Regards,
PharmEasy
Grievance – Order #653430280709210112-87065 - Issue with Teleconsultation

notes.body: Hello Rajdeep,     Greetings from PharmEasy!  We have received an update from our Teleconsultation team that the partner doctor tried calling on both the delivery and registered numbers, but they were unable to connect with you.      The prescription under the order is dated 2024, and it does not include all the medicines that were ordered. Therefore, a consultation was arranged to verify all the required medicines. We request that you keep your phone available when the call is placed, or place a new order using an active phone number, so that we can schedule the doctor’s consultation. You can also contact the numbers 080-46161170 or 080-61972566 from your delivery phone number.    Regards, PharmEasy
notes.body_html:

I had placed an order for Travacom 2.5 ml eye drops, but on 30th November, I received the incorrect product – Travoprost Ophthalmic Solution. I raised a return request on the same day; however, no pickup attempt has been made till now.

I have contacted your customer care team three times, requesting to be connected with a supervisor. Each time, I was assured that a supervisor would speak with me or call me back, but this has not happened. This lack of response and action has caused significant inconvenience.

1. Process my refund immediately, and

I trust that the grievance team will take this matter seriously and resolve it without further delay.

Thank you for your prompt attention.

Hello Prem,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

We understand your concern in regard to order #652682217628868608-70453.  

Due to the delay in pickup, a refund of Rs. 637.84 will be initiated to your account within 24-48 hours. Post initiation, the refund will be credited to your source account within 5-7 business days. Saturday, Sunday, and bank holidays are not included in this. 

Please note that the refund might not be shown in the UPI account and the same is credited to your bank account. Kindly check your bank account and wait till the above timeframe.
 
The item will be picked up once the service is available. We apologise for the inconvenience caused to you. Your patience is highly appreciated in the meantime.

Regards,

helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Hi All, 
This issue has been resolved. Reply has been sent. 

On Wed, Nov 26, 2025 at 12:49 PM Piyasa Roychowdhury <piyasa.roychowdhury@pharmeasy.in> wrote:
+ @Anuhya Kontheti 

On Wed, Nov 26, 2025 at 12:47 PM Jagdish Mishra <jagdish.mishra@pharmeasy.in> wrote:
Hi Grievance,

All variants of DOXTIL are removed from the website.

On Tue, Nov 25, 2025 at 5:59 PM Jagdish Mishra <jagdish.mishra@pharmeasy.in> wrote:
Hi Grievance,

Checking.

On Tue, Nov 25, 2025 at 5:25 PM Grievance Officer <grievance-officer@pharmeasy.in> wrote:
Team,

Kindly check.

Regards,
Grievance Helpdesk 


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Eeshani Sharma <esharma@rnaip.com>
Date: Tue, Nov 25, 2025 at 3:59 PM
Subject: Infringing listings of products under the impugned mark DOXTIL on pharmeasy.in [RNA Ref.: D4936-02367]
To: care@pharmeasy.in <care@pharmeasy.in>, Grievance Officer <grievance-officer@pharmeasy.in>
Cc: RNA Docketing <E-filing@rnaip.com>, Riya Raman <rraman@rnaip.com>, Eeshani Sharma <esharma@rnaip.com>, Tulika Mishra <tmishra@rnaip.com>


Our Ref.: D4936-02367/RN/ES                                           Without Prejudice                                     
November 25, 2025                                                                (By Email)
 
To,
Mr. Himanshu                                                                   
Grievance Officer,                                                                      
Axelia Solutions Private Limited, 
Office No. E1-509,
5th Floor, Kailas Esplanade Premises Co-op Society Ltd,
LBS Road, Ghatkopar West, Mumbai – 400086
 
Also at:
NA Elixir, 1st floor, No.100, 4th B Cross Road,
Koramangala Industrial Layout, Koramangala, Bengaluru- 560095
Email: care@pharmeasy.in; grievance-officer@pharmeasy.in
Phone: 08048641743

Re: Infringing listings of products under the impugned mark DOXTIL on pharmeasy.in
 
We write under instructions from and on behalf of Dr. Reddy's Laboratories Limited, having registered office at 8-2-337, Road No. 3, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana – 500034 (hereinafter referred to as “our client”) to address you as under:
 
  1. Our client is one of the largest pharmaceutical companies in India, and a well-established and reputed global entity engaged in the business of manufacturing, marketing and distribution of pharmaceutical, nutritional, and cosmetic products catering to the needs of patients and consumers both globally and in India. Our client on its own and through its affiliates is dedicated to providing impeccable quality healthcare and pharmaceutical products to its valued customers. The products manufactured and marketed by our client are sold under its well-known and famous trademarks and/or brand names and are known in India for their superior quality, technical excellence, and effectiveness.
 
  1. The trademark DOXT was honestly and independently coined by our client (and/or its predecessor) in the year 1976 and the same has been in use since its adoption. Product under the mark DOXT is used to treat various types of bacterial infections such as urinary tract infections, intestinal infections, respiratory infections, eye infections, gum infections, and sexually transmitted infections (like gonorrhea and syphilis). Medical products under the mark DOXT are extremely popular and are widely distributed all over India. The DOXT products are also sold on various other online e-pharmacy websites as well as on your website www.pharmeasy.in. The trademark DOXT has been continuously and extensively used, and on account of such use, the said trademark has acquired considerable goodwill and reputation as a quality medicinal product.
 
  1. Our client has also obtained registration of the mark DOXT as per details below:
S. No.
Trademark
Reg. No.
Reg. Date
Class
1.
DOXT
312333
11/02/1976
5
2.
Doxt-SL
2611552
14/10/2013
5

  1. On account of extensive use, the trademark DOXT has acquired tremendous goodwill and reputation in the market and acts as a source identifier. Thus, any unauthorised adoption or use of a mark containing DOXT by any third-party would violate our client’s proprietary rights.
 
  1. It has come to our client’s attention that identical products under the impugned mark DOXTIL, are listed and sold by Zodak Healthcare (hereinafter referred to as “opposite party”) on your platform www.pharmeasy.in. A table of the opposite party’s DOXTIL products along with the URLs of the listing on your platform is pasted below: 
 
S. No.
Product Name
URL
1.
Doxtil 200mg Tablets
https://pharmeasy.in/online-medicine-order/doxtil-200mg-tab-30066
2.
Doxtil OF Tablets
https://pharmeasy.in/online-medicine-order/doxtil-of-tab-102490
 
  1. Such use of the impugned mark DOXTIL is a clear act of bad faith and constitutes wilful and deliberate infringement of our client’s statutory and common law rights in the DOXT trademark. The impugned mark DOXTIL is deceptively and confusingly similar to the trademark DOXT. The opposite party has merely made cosmetic changes to our client’s trademark DOXT by adding the suffix ‘IL’ to derive the impugned mark, which is hardly a distinguishing factor. Further, the widespread use and reputable nature of our client’s trademark DOXT is common knowledge among consumers and those in medicinal and pharmaceutical trade.
 
  1. Further, our client also sells identical products under its DOXT trademark on your platform. The presence of the abovementioned infringing listing creates a high likelihood of confusion among consumers, who may mistakenly believe that the DOXTIL products are associated with our client or is a variant of our client’s DOXT brand, which is not the case. Our client has no control over quality of products offered under the impugned mark DOXTIL. In the business related to health, medicine and pharmaceuticals, any mishap or poor-quality products offered is bound to have devastating outcomes and would not only result in huge loss of goodwill and reputation in the trademark DOXT, but also put at risk the health of consumers and public at large, who would purchase the impugned products under the belief that the same emanates from our client.
 
  1. Such unauthorised use of the impugned mark DOXTIL is also contrary to your IP policies of pharmeasy.in, which prohibit the listing and sale of products that infringe upon third-party intellectual property rights. These policies underscore the platform’s commitment to protecting brand owners and maintaining a trustworthy marketplace.
 
  1. In view of the above, we request that you:
  1. Immediately remove all listings of the infringing products bearing the impugned mark DOXTIL from your platform; and
  2. Take appropriate measures to ensure that such listings are not permitted in the future.
 
  1. We trust that Pharmeasy being a responsible and reputed digital healthcare platform, you will take swift action in accordance with your IP policies and in the interest of consumer safety and business integrity. Our client is hopeful that its grievances will be addressed. Therefore, please revert to us within a period of 10 days from receipt of this letter or latest by December 05, 2025. 
 
  1. This letter is without prejudice to the assertion of our client’s any and all rights and remedies, all of which are reserved. If you have any queries concerning the above, please feel free to contact the undersigned immediately.
 
Yours truly,
 
Ranjan Narula | Eeshani Sharma
